{{Infobox royalty | name = Godji I | title = | titletext = | more = | type = | image = | image_size = | alt = | caption = | succession = [[Cutch State|Maharaja of Kutch]] | moretext = | reign = 1715 - 1718 | reign-type = | coronation = | cor-type = | predecessor =[[Pragmalji I]] | pre-type = | successor =[[Deshalji I]]
| birth_name = | birth_date = | birth_place = | death_date =1718 | death_place = | burial_date = | burial_place = | spouse = | spouse-type = Spouse | consort = | issue = [[Deshalji I]] | issue-link = | issue-pipe = | issue-type = | full name = | era name = | era dates = | regnal name = | posthumous name = | temple name = | house = [[Jadeja]] [[Rajput]] | house-type = Dynasty | father = [[Pragmalji I]] | mother = | religion = | occupation = | signature_type = | signature = }} Rao '''Godji I''' was the [[Raja|Rao]] of [[Cutch State|Cutch]] belonging to the [[Jadeja]] [[Rajput]] dynasty, who ruled [[Princely State of Cutch]] from 1715 to 1718.
==Life== Godji I was a son of Rao [[Pragmalji I]]. He led a force sent by his father to restore throne of Tamachi, the sixth in descent from their ancestor Hala, who was driven from [[Halar]]. After the death of Pragmalji, he succeeded in 1715 and ruled for a short period of three years. He desposed Haloji, the son of Pragmalji's elder brother Nagulji, of his estate of [[Mundra]]. Haloji, unable to resist, retired to Abdasa, and there founded the towns of [[Kothara, Kutch|Kothara]], Kotri, and Nagarchi. His descendants are known as Halani Jadejas. He died in 1718 and was succeeded by his son [[Deshalji I]].{{sfn | ''Gazetteer of the Bombay Presidency: Cutch, Palanpur, and Mahi Kantha'' | 2015 |page=137-138}}
