{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2013}} {{Infobox football biography | name = Kamel Ghilas | image = Kamel Ghilas.jpg | image_size = 220 | caption = Ghilas in 2012 | fullname = Kamel Fathi Ghilas<ref name="Hugman2010-11">{{cite book|editor-first=Barry J.|editor-last=Hugman|title=The PFA Footballers' Who's Who 2010–11|year=2010|publisher=Mainstream Publishing|location=Edinburgh|isbn=978-1-84596-601-0|page=165}}</ref> | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1984|3|9|df=y}} | birth_place = [[Marseille]], France | height = {{Height|m=1.77|precision=0}}<ref name="Hugman2010-11"/> | position = [[Forward (association football)|Forward]] | currentclub = | clubnumber = | youthyears1 = | youthclubs1 = | years1 = 2001–2003 | years2 = 2003–2006 | years3 = 2006–2008 | years4 = 2008–2009 | years5 = 2009–2012 | years6 = 2010–2011 | years7 = 2011–2012 | years8 = 2012–2014 | years9 = 2014 | clubs1 = Vitrolles | clubs2 = [[AS Cannes|Cannes]] | clubs3 = [[Vitória S.C.|Vitória Guimarães]] | clubs4 = [[Celta de Vigo|Celta]] | clubs5 = [[Hull City A.F.C.|Hull City]] | clubs6 = → [[AC Arles-Avignon|Arles-Avignon]] (loan) | clubs7 = → [[Stade de Reims|Reims]] (loan) | clubs8 = [[Stade de Reims|Reims]] | clubs9 = [[R. Charleroi S.C.|Charleroi]] | caps1 = 6 | caps2 = 86 | caps3 = 59 | caps4 = 33 | caps5 = 13 | caps6 = 19 | caps7 = 35 | caps8 = 24 | caps9 = 5 | goals1 = 1 | goals2 = 22 | goals3 = 18 | goals4 = 13 | goals5 = 1 | goals6 = 2 | goals7 = 14 | goals8 = 0 | goals9 = 0 | totalcaps = 280 | totalgoals = 71 | nationalyears1 = 2007–2012 | nationalteam1 = [[Algeria national football team|Algeria]] | nationalcaps1 = 19 | nationalgoals1 = 3 | club-update = 02:31, 5 May 2014 (UTC) | nationalteam-update = }}
'''Kamel Fathi Ghilas''' (born 9 March 1984) is an Algerian professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[forward (association football)|forward]].
==Club career== ===Early years=== Born in [[Marseille]], [[France]],<ref name="Hugman2010-11"/> Ghilas started his career in amateur football, with ES Vitrolles. At the age of 19 he joined [[AS Cannes]] in the [[Championnat National]], quickly breaking into the [[Glossary of association football terms#F|first team]] and featuring mostly as a [[Midfielder#Winger|winger]].
Ghilas established himself as a starter in the 2004–05 season, going on to lead the team in scoring by netting seven times in 31 appearances. The following year he contributed with 13 as the [[French Riviera]] club narrowly missed out on promotion to [[Ligue 2]], finishing two points behind [[FC Libourne-Saint-Seurin]] for the third and final spot.
===Vitória Guimarães=== Ghilas signed for [[Vitória S.C.]] from Portugal in the summer of 2006, penning a two-year contract.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.record.xl.pt/arquivo/interior.aspx?content_id=273522|title=Ghilas assinou por 2 anos|trans-title=Ghilas signed for 2 years|newspaper=[[Record (newspaper)|Record]]|language=Portuguese|date=15 June 2006|accessdate=16 December 2013}}</ref> In [[2006–07 Liga de Honra|his first year]] he ranked first in goals scored in his team, helping to a return to the [[Primeira Liga]] after one year out.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.record.xl.pt/arquivo/interior.aspx?content_id=337831|title=Ghilas: "Não estou cansado"|trans-title=Ghilas: "I am not tired"|newspaper=Record|language=Portuguese|date=28 March 2008|accessdate=16 December 2013}}</ref>
Ghilas made his debut in the competition on 19 August 2007, starting in a 1–1 home draw against [[Vitória F.C.|Vitória de Setúbal]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.gmrtv.pt/desporto/195-vitoria-comeca-liga-bwin-com-empate-caseiro-1-1|title=Vitória começa Liga Bwin com empate caseiro (1–1)|trans-title=Vitória start Bwin League with home draw (1–1)|publisher=Guimarães TV|language=Portuguese|date=20 August 2007|accessdate=9 April 2018}}</ref> He scored six times in a further 20 league appearances to help the side [[2007–08 Primeira Liga|finish a best-ever third]] and [[2008–09 UEFA Champions League|qualify]] to the [[UEFA Champions League]]; however, following a contract dispute, he left the [[Minho Province]] club as a [[free agent]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.record.xl.pt/arquivo/interior.aspx?content_id=343507|title=Direcção desiste da renovação de Ghilas|trans-title=Board of directors give up on Ghilas renewal|newspaper=Record|language=Portuguese|date=20 May 2008|accessdate=16 December 2013}}</ref>
===Celta=== On 12 July 2008, [[Celta de Vigo]] announced the signing of Ghilas from Vitória,<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.marca.com/edicion/marca/futbol/2a_division/celta/es/desarrollo/1145429.html|title=El Celta se adelanta al Arsenal y ficha a Kamel Ghilas|trans-title=Celta get ahead of Arsenal and sign Kamel Ghilas|newspaper=[[Marca (newspaper)|Marca]]|language=Spanish|date=12 July 2008|accessdate=12 July 2008}}</ref> with the player penning a three-year contract worth [[Euro|€]]300,000 a year.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.record.xl.pt/arquivo/interior.aspx?content_id=349963|title=Ghilas no Celta de Vigo para tentar a subida|trans-title=Ghilas in Celta de Vigo to attempt promotion|newspaper=Record|language=Portuguese|date=13 July 2008|accessdate=16 December 2013}}</ref> He scored his first goals for the [[Galicia (Spain)|Galicians]] on 28 September in a 2–1 home win over [[CD Tenerife]], in what was [[2008–09 Segunda División|the season]]'s first win.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.marca.com/edicion/marca/futbol/2a_division/cronica/es/desarrollo/1169841.html|title=El Celta consigue su primera victoria|trans-title=Celta get first win|newspaper=Marca|language=Spanish|date=28 September 2008|accessdate=10 October 2008}}</ref>
On 28 July 2009, a fee of [[Pound sterling|£]]1.7&nbsp;million was agreed for Ghilas to transfer to [[Blackburn Rovers F.C.|Blackburn Rovers]] in the [[Premier League]] – the move was set to be completed pending on the player agreeing personal terms and passing a medical. However, the transfer broke down in the 11th hour, with conflicting reports on the grounds: the English claimed he had failed the medical, whereas the Spaniards claimed that Blackburn had attempted to renegotiate the transfer fee and player's wages at the last minute; they attempted to disprove Rovers' claims by playing him in a [[Exhibition game|friendly]] the following day.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.atlantico.net/noticia/84036/celtadevigo/fichajes/ghilas/blackburnrovers/|title=La venta de Ghilas se rompe|trans-title=The sale of Ghilas breaks down|publisher=Atlántico|language=Spanish|date=31 July 2009|accessdate=31 July 2009|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090803182725/http://www.atlantico.net/noticia/84036/celtadevigo/fichajes/ghilas/blackburnrovers|archivedate=3 August 2009|df=dmy-all}}</ref>
===Hull City=== On 13 August 2009, Ghilas agreed terms with [[Hull City A.F.C.|Hull City]], signing a four-year deal for which Celta was paid roughly £2 million.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.espnfc.com/story/667229/readings-steven-hunt-signs-for-hullkamel-ghilas-follows|title=Reading's Hunt signs for Hull, Ghilas follows|publisher=[[ESPN FC|ESPN Soccernet]]|date=13 August 2009|accessdate=12 July 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-1206061/Hull-City-confirm-Kamel-Ghilas-signing-Celta-Vigo-striker-joins-reported-2m.html|title=Hull City confirm Kamel Ghilas signing as Celta Vigo striker joins for reported £2m|newspaper=[[Daily Mail]]|date=13 August 2009|accessdate=12 July 2017}}</ref> He made his debut for his new team nine days later, scoring in a 1–0 victory over [[Bolton Wanderers F.C.|Bolton Wanderers]] in the 61st minute after being fed a through ball from [[Jozy Altidore]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://soccernet.espn.go.com/gamecast?id=269888&cc=5901&league=ENG.1|title=Hull City 1–0 Bolton Wanderers|publisher=ESPN Soccernet|date=22 August 2009|accessdate=22 August 2009}}</ref>
However, Ghilas failed to perform for the [[East Riding of Yorkshire|East Yorkshire]] side subsequently, being loaned to French clubs [[AC Arles-Avignon]]<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.skysports.com/story/0,19528,11714_6286587,00.html|title=Tigers offload Ghilas on loan|publisher=[[Sky Sports]]|date=30 July 2010|accessdate=30 July 2010}}</ref> and [[Stade de Reims]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/14475584.stm|title=Hull sign Austrian winger Martin Pusic following trial|publisher=[[BBC Sport]]|date=10 August 2011|accessdate=10 August 2011}}</ref> He made his debut for the latter on 15 August 2011, netting in a 2–1 win over [[AS Monaco FC]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.dzfoot.com/news-9702/verts-premiere-reussie-pour-ghilas-contre-monaco/|title=Verts: Première réussie pour Ghilas contre Monaco|trans-title=Greens: First strike for Ghilas against Monaco|publisher=DZFoot|language=French|date=15 August 2011|accessdate=16 December 2013}}</ref>
===Late career=== [[File:Kamel Ghilas (ACA).jpg|thumb|200px|Ghilas lining up for [[Stade de Reims|Reims]] in 2012]] After scoring 14 goals in the [[2011–12 Ligue 2|2011–12 campaign]], being an essential offensive unit as Reims returned to [[Ligue 1]] after more than three decades, Ghilas joined the club on a permanent deal.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://uk.eurosport.yahoo.com/news/ghilas-leaves-hull-reims-164341297.html|title=Ghilas leaves Hull for Reims|publisher=[[Yahoo Sports]]|date=6 July 2012|accessdate=18 August 2012|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20130105090633/http://uk.eurosport.yahoo.com/news/ghilas-leaves-hull-reims-164341297.html|archivedate=5 January 2013}}</ref> On 30 January 2014 he moved teams and countries again, joining [[Belgian Pro League]]'s [[R. Charleroi S.C.]] for six months.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.sporting-charleroi.be/actualite-detail.php?id=2211|title=L’international Algérien Kamel Ghilas attaquant au Sporting.|trans-title=Algerian international forward Kamel Ghilas at Sporting.|publisher=Sporting Charleroi|language=French|date=30 January 2014|accessdate=31 January 2014}}</ref>
==International career== Although French-born, Ghilas opted to represent [[Algeria national football team|Algeria]], making his international debut on 2 June 2007 in an [[2008 Africa Cup of Nations]] [[2008 Africa Cup of Nations qualification|qualifier]] against [[Cape Verde national football team|Cape Verde]]. Five months later he scored his first goal, in a 3–2 friendly win over [[Mali national football team|Mali]].
